        <link href="CrossReferenceIndex.dita#task_upv_ypt_ht" class="- topic/link " xtrf="file:/Users/ilovan/CWRC%20Documentation%20-%20everything/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="link:5;91:64" type="task"><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext ">Creating cross referencing index terms</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Cross referencing allows you to draw connections between terms found in different         sections or chapters of your document. </desc></link>
        <link href="UploadDocDToC.dita#task_grd_sqt_ht" class="- topic/link " xtrf="file:/Users/ilovan/CWRC%20Documentation%20-%20everything/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="link:6;92:58" type="task"><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext ">Uploading your XML document to DToC</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc "> The information below is for an XML         document that follows the template structure. </desc></link>
        <link href="UploadTextURL.dita#task_stp_1wt_ht" class="- topic/link " xtrf="file:/Users/ilovan/CWRC%20Documentation%20-%20everything/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="link:7;93:58" type="task"><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext ">Uploading text and URLs into DToC</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Some features will be unavailable using this method (like the index). </desc></link>
        <link href="OverviewDToC.dita#reference_bfm_blm_lt" class="- topic/link " xtrf="file:/Users/ilovan/CWRC%20Documentation%20-%20everything/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="link:8;94:62" type="reference"><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext ">Overview of Dynamic Table of Contexts</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">The Dynamic Table of Contexts (DToC) viewer is an in-browser e-reader that uses the     underlying structure of a document to allow different paths through the text to be discovered when     read. The corpus may be navigated via semantic tags, the index (if present), or the search function,     as well as through the frequency of terms used throughout the document. DToC allows readers to "curate" the     text they are reading by permitting the customization of tags, even if the text being "read" is not their own. It     is also possible to make one's own DToC edition by starting from one of our templates.</desc></link>
        <link href="XMLTemplatesRef.dita#reference_vx1_1pk_nt" class="- topic/link " xtrf="file:/Users/ilovan/CWRC%20Documentation%20-%20everything/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="link:9;95:65" type="reference"><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext ">XML templates</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc "> Please feel free to download the DToC XML template or ignore it, depending on your XML     expertise and/or adventurous spirit.</desc></link>
